An Eskom logo is seen at the entrance of their head offices in Sunninghill, Sandton. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has won a high court case against energy regulator, National Energy Regulator of South Africa (Nersa). The legal battle victory allows Eskom to recover costs incurred during the 2019 financial year. READ:Â Load-shedding moves to Stage 4 The power utility had asked Nersa for a tariff increase that would allow it to generate over R219-billion in revenue. Nersa's allowed for increases that would amount to just over R190-billion. Eskom has 60 days to apply to the regulator to increase the tariffs.